# .cursorignore preset — EDGE focus
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PURPOSE
# Use this preset when you are actively working on the edge-server codebase.
# It excludes cloud RAG, Gradio UIs, and infra files from Cursor's context to
# reduce noise and speed up assistance. Copy or symlink this file to
# repo-root `.cursorignore` when focusing on edge tasks.
#
# IMPORTANT: Cursor only reads the root-level `.cursorignore`. Files under
# `.cursor/presets/` are templates only; they have no effect until copied to
# the root as `.cursorignore`.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Focus on edge-server — ignore cloud, gradio, and infra
apps/cloud-rag/**
apps/gradio/**
infra/**

# General heavy/noise files and directories (keep context small and clean)
**/__pycache__/**
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/*.pyd
**/*.log
**/*.tmp
**/*.bin

# Data/artifacts commonly large
**/faiss_index/**
**/data/**
**/*.sqlite
.coverage

# Re-include key documents and rules even if matched above
!PRD.md
!.cursor/.cursorrules
!TASKS.md

# Optional: keep tests included to guide development
# (Comment the next line if you want to exclude tests temporarily.)
#!tests/**
